Top Stories (March 7)

DTE ENERGY ESTIMATES REFLECT CLOSE OF MCN ENERGY MERGER
DTE Energy Co. projects 2001 earnings of $2.90 to $3.00 a diluted share, 
reflecting the planned $2.24 billion acquisition of MCN Energy Group Inc.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
03/07/eng-djn/eng-djn_150227_166_617440111004

PACIFIC NORTHWEST OFFICIALS WANT REGULATORS TO ACT ON SOARING POWER RATES
In December 1999, Seattle City Light paid an average of $34 for each megawatt 
hour of electricity purchased on regional wholesale markets. A year later, 
the utility was paying an average of $323 per megawatt hour.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/03/07/krtbn/0000-0370-SE-POWER

COMPETITION IS SLOW TO ARRIVE IN PENNSYLVANIA'S NATURAL-GAS MARKET
Peco Energy Co. announced last week that it was raising suburban natural-gas 
rates by 25 percent -- and there was little a residential customer could do 
about it.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/03/07/krtbn/0000-0310-PH-NATL-GAS

NYSEG PROPOSES ELECTRIC PRICE PROTECTION PLAN THAT FREEZES RATES AND ASSURES 
ENERGY RELIABILITY
New York State Electric & Gas Corporation, a wholly-owned subsidiary of 
Energy East , today sent a letter to the New York Public Service Commission 
that proposes a seven year electric price protection plan for electric 
consumers in upstate New York.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/comtex/2
001/03/07/pr/0000-4150-ny-nyseg-proposes

ORION POWER BEGINS CONSTRUCTION OF 374 MEGAWATT POWER PLANT IN PITTSBURGH
Orion Power MidWest, L.P., a subsidiary of Orion Power Holdings, Inc., 
announced today that it has received all necessary permits to begin 
construction to modernize its Brunot Island Generating Station located near 
downtown Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/comtex/2
001/03/07/pr/0000-8683-md-orion-pwr-construt

